  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 1280 mg
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: Middle East
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/curried-chickpea-burgers-66c6243f5cb721784e63849e
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring @butter{1%tbsp} to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Peel and mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens; mince whites. Pick and mince fronds from @dill{1/4%ounce}. Thinly slice @tomato{1} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cut @broccoli{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. (Save potatoes for another use.)

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Swap in broccoli for potatoes; roast 12-15 minutes.

== Tangy Mayo ==

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, @apricot jam{1%unit}, half the @turmeric{1%tsp}, and @white wine vinegar{2%tsp} until combined. (Be sure to measure the vinegar—we sent more.) Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> We sent more vinegar to measure if needed.

== Chickpea Burgers ==

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%unit}. Place half the chickpeas in a #large bowl{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until almost smooth.

> It's OK if there are some larger pieces.

Stir in @garlic{}, scallion whites, half the scallion greens, half the dill, half the @curry powder{1%tbsp}, @tempura batter{3%tbsp}, and @water{2%tbsp} until thoroughly combined. Taste and season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and pepper.

Divide chickpea mixture into two mounds.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Using a #spatula{}, add chickpea mounds to pan and gently press to flatten into patties (rub a little oil on the bottom of the spatula to prevent sticking), each about as wide as a burger bun.

Cook patties until golden brown and crisp, ~{3-4%minutes} per side. (Add more oil when flipping the patties if needed.) Transfer to a #plate{}.

== Assembly ==

Meanwhile, halve and toast @brioche buns{2} until golden; spread softened butter onto cut sides of bottom buns.

Spread top buns with as much tangy mayo as you like. Fill buns with chickpea patties and tomato.

Divide chickpea burgers and potato wedges between plates. Sprinkle potatoes with remaining scallion greens and remaining dill. Serve with remaining tangy mayo on the side for dipping.

> We heart you! Enjoy with roasted potato wedges on the side.